#  Basic Penetration Testing Simulation

##  Objective

Simulate a basic penetration testing workflow:
- Enumeration
- Scanning
- Web testing
- Basic exploitation concepts

---

##  Step 1 – Reconnaissance (Nmap Scan)

```bash
nmap -sV 10.10.10.5

Result:
Port 22 → SSH (OpenSSH)
Port 80 → HTTP (Apache)


 Step 2 – Directory Enumeration (Gobuster)
gobuster dir -u http://10.10.10.5 -w common.txt

Result:
/admin
/login
/config.php


 Step 3 – Web Testing (Burp Suite)

Example:

GET /login?user=admin&pass=123


 Step 4 – SQL Injection Testing (SQLMap)
sqlmap -u "http://10.10.10.5/page.php?id=1" --dbs


 Step 5 – Exploitation (Conceptual)
use exploit/multi/handler


 Step 6 – Password Attack
john hashes.txt


 Step 7 – Defensive Perspective
Logs analysis
Identifying suspicious activity


